org.sakaiproject.taggable.api

Interface TagList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<Tag>, Iterable<Tag>, List<Tag>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TagListImpl

    public interface TagList
extends List<Tag>
    A specialized list that can provide column information in the form of a TagColumn for each field that the Tag objects in the list can provide.
    Author:
    The Sakai Foundation.
    See Also:
    Tag

      • sort

        void sort(TagColumn column,
        boolean ascending)
        Method to sort the Tag objects in this list by the fields represented by the given TagColumn.
        Parameters:
        column - The tag column to sort by. This may be null, indicating a default sort column.
        ascending - True if the objects should be assorted in ascending order, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        Tag#getField(String), Tag.getFields()
